definition: bird/CL:隻|只[zhi1],群[qun2]/(dialect) to pay attention to/(intensifier) damned/goddam

sentences.english: Hummingbirds were stopping over honeysuckles flowers.
In the world where the humming-bird flashed ahead of creation.
sentences.chinese: 在這世界裏，蜂鳥卻閃現於萬物之前。

sentences.english: The tiniest green hummingbird in the world?
sentences.chinese: 看世界上最小的綠色蜂鳥？

sentences.english: Researchers believe that some hummingbirds fly non-stop over the Gulf of Mexico.
sentences.chinese: 研究員相信，一些蜂鳥會馬不停蹄地飛越墨西哥灣。

sentences.english: Their 10 guilder bill depicts a hummingbird on geometric patterns.
sentences.chinese: 10荷蘭盾紙幣顯示蜂鳥與幾何圖案。

sentences.english: Hummingbirds have stiletto - like bills to probe the deepest nectar - bearing flowers.
sentences.chinese: 蜂鳥有鑽孔錐一樣的喙來探進有花蜜花朵的最深處。

sentences.english: Anna's hummingbirdSlow-motion footage has revealed how a hovering hummingbird is able to cope with wet weather.
sentences.chinese: 慢動作鏡頭揭示了盤旋中的蜂鳥是如何應付雨水的。

sentences.english: When the hummingbird came inside, I closed thd door behind him, then set up another feeder.
sentences.chinese: 蜂鳥飛進去後，我關上門，又放好一個食具。

sentences.english: It seemed to him that he beheld a humming-bird in the midst of toads .
sentences.chinese: 他好象在癩蛤蟆羣裏見到一隻蜂鳥。

sentences.english: Hummingbirds have stiletto-like bills to probe the deepest nectar-bearing flowers.
sentences.chinese: 蜂鳥有鑽孔錐一樣的喙來探進有花蜜花朵的最深處。

sentences.english: If you feed hummingbirds, remember sugar-syrup spills will attract loads of ants and other insect pests.
sentences.chinese: 如果你喂蜂鳥，記住糖蜜會吸引螞蟻和其他害蟲。

sentences.english: Marvels of micro-engineering, hummingbirds are the bird world's featherweight champions.
sentences.chinese: 微型工程的奇蹟，蜂鳥是鳥類世界的輕量級冠軍。

sentences.english: Why do hummingbirds and gorillas both have backbones ?
sentences.chinese: 爲什麼蜂鳥和大猩猩都有脊骨？

sentences.english: The weight of a hummingbird. Twentyone grams- and perhaps also of a human soul.
sentences.chinese: 五個硬幣，一隻蜂鳥，或是一塊巧克力。
